value.name: Group Identification
value.description: Identifier assigned by the merchant identifying a set of POI terminals performing some categories of transactions.

value.name: Card Reading Capabilities
value.description: Card reading capabilities of the POI performing the transaction.

value.name: Cardholder Verification Capabilities
value.description: Cardholder verification capabilities of the POI performing the transaction.

value.name: On Line Capabilities
value.description: On-line and off-line capabilities of the POI.

value.name: Display Type
value.description: Type of display (for example merchant or cardholder).

value.name: Number Of Lines
value.description: Number of lines of the display component.

value.name: Line Width
value.description: Number of columns of the display component.

value.name: Display Capabilities
value.description: Capabilities of the display components performing the transaction.

value.name: Print Line Width
value.description: Number of columns of the printer component.

value.name: Capabilities
value.description: Capabilities of the POI performing the transaction.

value.name: POI Component Type
value.description: Type of component belonging to a POI Terminal.

value.name: Manufacturer Identification
value.description: Identification of the software, hardware or system provider of the POI component.

value.name: Model
value.description: Identification of a model of POI component for a given manufacturer.

value.name: Version Number
value.description: Version of component belonging to a given model.

value.name: Serial Number
value.description: Serial number of a component.

value.name: Approval Number
value.description: Unique approval number for a component, delivered by a certification body. Usage: More than one approval number could be present, when assigned by different bodies. The certification body identification must be provided within the approval number (for example at the beginning of the value).

value.name: Component
value.description: Data related to a component of the POI performing the transaction.

value.name: POI
value.description: Physical or logical card payment terminal containing software and hardware components.

value.name: Additional Service
value.description: Service in addition to the main service.

value.name: Transaction Category
value.description: Category code conform to ISO 18245, related to the type of services or goods the merchant provides for the transaction.

value.name: Sale Reconciliation Identification
value.description: Unique identification of the sales reconciliation period between the acceptor and the acquirer. This identification might be linked to the identification of the settlement for further verification by the merchant.

value.name: First Transaction
value.description: CardSequenceNumberRange1: FirstTransactionSequenceNumberMessage element to be finalised once feedback from Card SEG has been received.

value.name: Last Transaction
value.description: CardSequenceNumberRange1: LastTransactionSequenceNumberMessage element to be finalised once feedback from Card SEG has been received.

value.name: Sequence Number Range
value.description: Range of sequence numbers on which the globalisation applies.

value.name: From Date
value.description: Start date of the range.

value.name: To Date
value.description: End date of the range.

value.name: Date
value.description: Period expressed with dates.

value.name: From Date Time
value.description: Date and time at which the range starts.

value.name: To Date Time
value.description: Date and time at which the range ends.

value.name: Date Time
value.description: Period expressed a dates and times.

value.name: Transaction Date Range
value.description: Date range on which the globalisation applies.

value.name: Aggregated
value.description: Card transaction details, based on card transaction aggregated data performed by the card acquirer.

value.name: ICC Related Data
value.description: Data related to an integrated circuit card application.

value.name: Card Present
value.description: Indicates whether the transaction has been initiated by a card physically present or not.

value.name: Cardholder Present
value.description: Indicates whether the transaction has been initiated in presence of the cardholder or not.

value.name: On Line Context
value.description: On-line or off-line context of the transaction.

value.name: Attendance Context
value.description: Human attendance at the POI location during the transaction.

value.name: Transaction Environment
value.description: Indicates the environment of the transaction.

value.name: Transaction Channel
value.description: Identifies the type of the communication channels used by the cardholder to the acceptor system.

value.name: Attendant Message Capable
value.description: Indicates whether a message can be sent or not on an attendant display (attendant display present or not).

value.name: Attendant Language
value.description: Language used to display messages to the attendant.

value.name: Card Data Entry Mode
value.description: Entry mode of the card data.

value.name: Fallback Indicator
value.description: Indicator of a card entry mode fallback.

value.name: Authentication Method
value.description: Method used to authenticate the cardholder.

value.name: Authentication Entity
value.description: Entity or object in charge of verifying the cardholder authenticity.

value.name: Authentication Method
value.description: Method used to authenticate a cardholder.

value.name: Payment Context
value.description: Context of the card payment transaction.

value.name: Additional Service
value.description: Service in addition to the main service.

value.name: Transaction Category
value.description: Category code conform to ISO 18245, related to the type of services or goods the merchant provides for the transaction. This element is also known as the MerchantCategoryCode.

value.name: Sale Reconciliation Identification
value.description: Unique identification of the sales reconciliation period between the acceptor and the acquirer. This identification might be linked to the identification of the settlement for further verification by the merchant.

value.name: Sale Reference Number
value.description: Unique reference of the sales as provided by the merchant.

value.name: Re Presentment Reason
value.description: Reason for representment of a card transaction.

value.name: Sequence Number
value.description: Sequential number of the card transaction, as assigned by the POI (Point of Interaction).  Usage: The sequential number is increased incrementally for each transaction.

value.name: Transaction Date Time
value.description: Local date and time of the transaction assigned by the POI (Point Of Interaction).

value.name: Transaction Reference
value.description: Identification of the transaction that has to be unique for a time period.

value.name: Transaction Identification
value.description: Identification of the transaction assigned by the POI (Point Of Interaction).

value.name: Product Code
value.description: Product code of the item purchased.

value.name: Unit Of Measure
value.description: Unit of measure of the item purchased.

value.name: Product Quantity
value.description: Product quantity.

value.name: Unit Price
value.description: Price per unit of product.

value.name: Product Amount
value.description: Monetary value of purchased product.

value.name: Tax Type
value.description: Information on tax paid on the product.

value.name: Additional Product Information
value.description: Additional information related to the product.

value.name: Product
value.description: Product purchased with the transaction.

value.name: Validation Date
value.description: Date when the deposit was validated by the financial institution that collected the cash.

value.name: Validation Sequence Number
value.description: Sequential number of the validation of the cash deposit. Usage: The sequential number is increased incrementally for each transaction.

value.name: Individual
value.description: Card transaction details for the individual transaction, as recorded at the POI (point of interaction).

value.name: Transaction
value.description: Card transaction details, which can be either globalised by the acquirer or individual transaction.

value.name: IBAN
value.description: International Bank Account Number (IBAN) - identifier used internationally by financial institutions to uniquely identify the account of a customer. Further specifications of the format and content of the IBAN can be found in the standard ISO 13616 "Banking and related financial services - International Bank Account Number (IBAN)" version 1997-10-01, or later revisions.

value.name: Identification
value.description: Identification assigned by an institution.

value.name: Code
value.description: Name of the identification scheme, in a coded form as published in an external list.

value.name: Proprietary
value.description: Name of the identification scheme, in a free text form.

value.name: Scheme Name
value.description: Name of the identification scheme.

value.name: Issuer
value.description: Entity that assigns the identification.

value.name: Other
value.description: Unique identification of an account, as assigned by the account servicer, using an identification scheme.

value.name: Identification
value.description: Unique and unambiguous identification for the account between the account owner and the account servicer.

value.name: Code
value.description: Account type, in a coded form.

value.name: Proprietary
value.description: Nature or use of the account in a proprietary form.

value.name: Type
value.description: Specifies the nature, or use of the account.

value.name: Currency
value.description: Identification of the currency in which the account is held.  Usage: Currency should only be used in case one and the same account number covers several currencies and the initiating party needs to identify which currency needs to be used for settlement on the account.

value.name: Name
value.description: Name of the account, as assigned by the account servicing institution, in agreement with the account owner in order to provide an additional means of identification of the account. Usage: The account name is different from the account owner name. The account name is used in certain user communities to provide a means of identifying the account, in addition to the account owner's identity and the account number.

value.name: Pre Paid Account
value.description: Prepaid account for the transfer or loading of an amount of money.

value.name: Card Transaction
value.description: Provides the data related to the card (number, scheme), terminal (number, identification) and transactional data used to uniquely identify a card transaction.

value.name: Additional Transaction Information
value.description: Further details of the transaction.

value.name: Place And Name
value.description: Unambiguous reference to the location where the supplementary data must be inserted in the message instance. In the case of XML, this is expressed by a valid XPath.

value.name: Envelope
value.description: Technical element wrapping the supplementary data.

value.name: Supplementary Data
value.description: Additional information that cannot be captured in the structured elements and/or any other specific block.

value.name: Transaction Details
value.description: Provides information on the underlying transaction(s).

value.name: Entry Details
value.description: Provides details on the entry.

value.name: Additional Entry Information
value.description: Further details of the entry.

value.name: Entry
value.description: Specifies an entry in the debit credit notification. Usage: At least one reference must be provided to identify the entry and its underlying transaction(s). Usage Rule: In case of a Payments R-transaction the creditor / debtor referenced of the original payment initiation messages is also used for reporting of the R-transaction. The original debtor/creditor in the reporting of R-Transactions is not inverted.  Following elements all defined in the TransactionDetails in RelatedParties or RelatedAgents are impacted by this usage rule: Creditor, UltimateCreditor, CreditorAccount, CreditorAgent, Debtor, UltimateDebtor, DebtorAccount and DebtorAgent.

value.name: Additional Notification Information
value.description: Further details of the account notification.

value.name: Notification
value.description: Notifies debit and credit entries for the account.

value.name: Place And Name
value.description: Unambiguous reference to the location where the supplementary data must be inserted in the message instance. In the case of XML, this is expressed by a valid XPath.

value.name: Envelope
value.description: Technical element wrapping the supplementary data.

value.name: Supplementary Data
value.description: Additional information that cannot be captured in the structured elements and/or any other specific block.
